‚úÖ TOP RAG INTERVIEW QUESTIONS ‚Äî Explained in Simple Words
1Ô∏è‚É£ What is RAG?

RAG = Retrieval-Augmented Generation
It means:

üëâ LLM + External Knowledge

The model retrieves relevant documents and then generates better answers.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Why do we use RAG?

Because LLMs don't know everything.
RAG helps in:

‚úî reducing hallucination
‚úî using private data
‚úî improving accuracy

3Ô∏è‚É£ What are the main steps in RAG?

Embedding text ‚Üí into numbers

Store embeddings ‚Üí in vector DB

Search relevant chunks

LLM generates final answer using retrieved data

4Ô∏è‚É£ What is Vector Database?

A database that stores embeddings and allows similarity search.

Examples: FAISS, Pinecone, Chroma, Weaviate.

Simple:
üëâ ‚ÄúGoogle search inside your own data.‚Äù

5Ô∏è‚É£ What are embeddings?

Embeddings are numerical vectors representing meaning of text.

Example:
‚ÄúApple‚Äù (fruit) and ‚Äúbanana‚Äù ‚Üí close in embedding space.

6Ô∏è‚É£ What is chunking?

Breaking big documents into small pieces.

Why?
LLM cannot take 200-page PDF in one go.

7Ô∏è‚É£ What is vector search?

Searching similar meaning instead of exact words.

Example:
Query: ‚ÄúHow to recharge battery?‚Äù
Match: ‚ÄúSteps to charge your device.‚Äù

8Ô∏è‚É£ What are the components of a RAG system?

Document loader

Text splitter

Embedding model

Vector database

Retriever

LLM

9Ô∏è‚É£ What is a retriever?

It selects the most relevant chunks from the vector DB.

Example:
Top-3 similar chunks.

1Ô∏è‚É£0Ô∏è‚É£ Difference between RAG and fine-tuning?
RAG	Fine-tuning
Adds external knowledge	Changes the model
Cheap	Expensive
No training needed	Training needed
Flexible	Less flexible
1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ When should you use RAG?

Use RAG when you need:

‚úî private data
‚úî updated information
‚úî fast changes
‚úî cost-efficient solution

1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ When NOT to use RAG?

‚ùå Data is extremely structured
‚ùå User queries require heavy reasoning
‚ùå Data changes every second

1Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ What is Hybrid Search?

Combination of:

semantic search

keyword search

Helps when user needs exact keywords.

1Ô∏è‚É£4Ô∏è‚É£ What is metadata filtering?

Filtering search results based on tags.

Example:
Only show documents of 2024 or HR department.

1Ô∏è‚É£5Ô∏è‚É£ What is re-ranking?

After retrieving top chunks, a model re-orders them to pick the best ones.

1Ô∏è‚É£6Ô∏è‚É£ What is context window?

The maximum amount of text an LLM can take as input.

RAG helps by reducing irrelevant text.

1Ô∏è‚É£7Ô∏è‚É£ What is hallucination in LLM?

When LLM makes up fake answers.
RAG reduces this by giving real documents.

1Ô∏è‚É£8Ô∏è‚É£ What is Retrieval Pipeline?

All steps from query ‚Üí retrieval ‚Üí LLM answer.

1Ô∏è‚É£9Ô∏è‚É£ What is multi-vector RAG?

Using multiple embeddings per chunk:

Title

Paragraph

Keywords

Entities

Better retrieval accuracy.

2Ô∏è‚É£0Ô∏è‚É£ What is multi-modal RAG?

RAG using:

text

images

PDFs

audio

tables

Example: Searching inside scanned PDFs.

2Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ What is query expansion?

Automatically expanding user query.

Query: "loan eligibility"
Expanded: "loan rules", "home loan eligibility", "bank document requirements"

2Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ What is chunk overlap?

Small overlapping text so context isn‚Äôt lost.

2Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ What is BM25 (traditional search)?

A keyword-based retrieval algorithm.
Useful for exact match queries.

2Ô∏è‚É£4Ô∏è‚É£ RAG vs. Search Engine?

Search engine ‚Üí retrieves only

RAG ‚Üí retrieves + LLM generates answer

2Ô∏è‚É£5Ô∏è‚É£ What is negative sampling in RAG training?

Selecting irrelevant documents to improve retriever training.

26Ô∏è‚É£ What are the challenges in RAG?

Bad chunking

Wrong embeddings

Irrelevant retrieval

Too much or too little context

Slow search in huge DB

27Ô∏è‚É£ How to evaluate RAG?

Metrics:

Retrieval precision

Relevance score

Answer correctness

Context overlap

28Ô∏è‚É£ What is LLM-as-a-Judge?

Using an LLM to check if retrieved documents are accurate.

29Ô∏è‚É£ How to optimize RAG?

Better chunking

Re-ranking

Hybrid search

Metadata filters

Smaller & faster embeddings

30Ô∏è‚É£ What is end-to-end RAG evaluation?

Evaluate:

Retrieval quality

Answer quality

Ground truth matching

üéØ BONUS: 30-second interview reply

You can say:

‚ÄúRAG is a method where an LLM retrieves relevant information from a vector database and uses it to generate an accurate answer. It reduces hallucinations and allows models to use private or updated data. A RAG pipeline includes chunking, embedding, storing in a vector DB, retrieving, and LLM generation.‚Äù
